The paper deals with rate-distortion functions and coding techniques for multiple descriptions of colored Gaussian sources. This falls under the domain of information theory (cs.IT) and multimedia (cs.MM), as well as signal processing (cs.SP) and machine learning (cs.LG) since the paper proposes a new representation for the test channel and uses variational calculus to obtain a spectral domain representation. Additionally, the paper discusses the design of the coding scheme, which could fall under the sub-category of systems and control (cs.SI).
